snippet: A joint session of Congress certified the results of November's presidential election Friday, declaring President Obama and Vice President Joseph R. Biden Jr. the winners with 332 electoral votes.
abstract: A joint session of Congress certified the results of November's presidential election Friday, declaring President Obama and Vice President Joseph R. Biden Jr. the winners with 332 electoral votes.

headline.main: The Mahogany Boxes Hold No Surprises From the Electoral College
